      {"heading": "Notes: Mark 13:1-8", "content": "<p>Jesus talks surprisingly often in a way that seems to give creation feelings, even if in a metaphorical way. He talks about stones crying out, and here he describes the birth pangs of the earth as they await the renewal of everything. I wonder how often we think about creation as having its own relationship to God, separate from our interaction with it? Certainly, the psalmist seems to talk that way!</p>"}
